radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated with wall thickening and adjacent fat stranding, measuring up to 8 mm. Within the proximal lumen of the appendix is a calcified appendicolith. The lung bases are clear, and the liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, ureters, stomach, and loops of small bowel appear unremarkable. No adjacent fluid collection or evidence of extraluminal gas to suggest perforation is seen.
